Dear Hiring Committee,

I am writing to express my interest in the Assistant Registrar for Reporting, Registration, and Credentials position at Arapahoe Community College. With a strong background in student records, enrollment services, and direct student support, I am motivated by the opportunity to contribute to ACC’s mission of providing accessible, accurate, and student-centered registration and credentialing services.

In my current/previous role as IT Work Study at Arapahoe Community College, I have supported students through complex academic processes including transcript evaluation, registration troubleshooting, graduation review, and records management. I routinely work with students, faculty, and campus partners to resolve escalated issues in a timely and compassionate manner, ensuring compliance with institutional policy, FERPA, and federal and state regulations. This experience has strengthened my attention to detail, ability to manage competing deadlines, and commitment to delivering clear, solution-focused communication.

I also bring experience maintaining and utilizing student information systems and reporting tools to improve operational efficiency and data integrity. My work has included [example: running degree audits, maintaining academic records, analyzing enrollment data, or producing reports for leadership], as well as frequent use of Microsoft Excel to track, reconcile, and analyze student data. I enjoy applying data literacy skills to identify process improvements that enhance both student success and departmental effectiveness.

Equity, inclusion, and access are central to my professional practice. I have worked closely with students from diverse backgrounds, including first-generation students, veterans, students with disabilities, and students from historically marginalized communities. In these roles, I strive to create welcoming and respectful environments by practicing active listening, using inclusive communication, and advocating for equitable solutions within established policies. This commitment means ensuring that institutional processes are transparent, understandable, and supportive—especially for students navigating higher education systems for the first time.

I am particularly drawn to ACC because of its emphasis on student-centered leadership, collaboration, and continuous improvement within Records and Enrollment Services. I would welcome the opportunity to contribute my organizational skills, problem-solving abilities, and dedication to inclusive student support to the Assistant Registrar role.

Thank you for your time and consideration. I look forward to the possibility of discussing how my experience and values align with the needs of Arapahoe Community College.

